1
00:01:35,759 --> 00:01:38,310
[Too Young To Love]

2
00:01:38,410 --> 00:01:41,259
[Episode 23]

3
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,039
Why that laugh?

4
00:01:49,759 --> 00:01:50,890
Just now when we were

5
00:01:51,890 --> 00:01:53,750
pretending to still be together,

6
00:01:53,810 --> 00:01:54,410
did you see

7
00:01:54,420 --> 00:01:55,800
the look on their faces?

8
00:02:02,150 --> 00:02:03,070
Well,

9
00:02:03,830 --> 00:02:05,040
if they knew

10
00:02:09,150 --> 00:02:11,400
we had already broken up,

11
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:13,250
what would they say?

12
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:28,910
I think

13
00:02:29,890 --> 00:02:31,010
they would say,

14
00:02:33,470 --> 00:02:34,520
"Is it true?"

15
00:02:37,430 --> 00:02:39,470
"They were such a perfect couple

16
00:02:40,050 --> 00:02:41,610
made for each other.

17
00:02:42,570 --> 00:02:44,430
And they just broke up like that?"

18
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,470
"Back then,

19
00:02:49,230 --> 00:02:50,350
if Yi Lan

20
00:02:50,930 --> 00:02:52,060
hadn't gone abroad,

21
00:02:53,430 --> 00:02:55,630
they probably wouldn't have broken up.

22
00:02:57,230 --> 00:02:59,110
If Tong Xiaole

23
00:02:59,630 --> 00:03:01,390
had gone abroad with Yi Lan,

24
00:03:03,380 --> 00:03:05,100
they definitely would still be together.

25
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:07,070
♪ By not thinking about it or guessing ♪

26
00:03:07,540 --> 00:03:09,110
Perhaps they would be

27
00:03:07,590 --> 00:03:10,500
♪ I thought I could break free ♪

28
00:03:10,390 --> 00:03:11,860
married by now.

29
00:03:10,770 --> 00:03:17,050
♪ Time has shown
I'm not as carefree as I imagined ♪

30
00:03:13,470 --> 00:03:15,230
They might even have kids.

31
00:03:18,190 --> 00:03:19,420
And their kids

32
00:03:19,260 --> 00:03:23,220
♪ I still can't forget the tenderness
you gave me that year ♪

33
00:03:22,540 --> 00:03:23,829
might even have

34
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:26,930
♪ Exhausting all my strength,
I still can't fool myself ♪

35
00:03:24,420 --> 00:03:26,420
their own childhood sweethearts."

36
00:03:27,410 --> 00:03:30,480
♪ Your place is still here ♪

37
00:03:30,730 --> 00:03:34,470
♪ No one else can take it ♪

38
00:03:35,230 --> 00:03:38,820
♪ Let me treat it as just a heavy rain ♪

39
00:03:39,030 --> 00:03:43,640
♪ Gradually, the memories we've built
become clear ♪

40
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:48,110
♪ All composed into a song ♪

41
00:03:49,350 --> 00:03:52,590
♪ It's still so beautiful ♪

42
00:04:00,670 --> 00:04:01,230
Yi Lan,

43
00:04:03,220 --> 00:04:04,100
if...

44
00:04:06,540 --> 00:04:08,370
we hadn't broken up back then,

45
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:12,990
♪ Every warm touch that drew us closer ♪

46
00:04:12,420 --> 00:04:14,820
wouldn't we still be happy right now?

47
00:04:14,290 --> 00:04:16,180
♪ Was nothing but a dream ♪

48
00:04:16,490 --> 00:04:19,140
♪ So many sunrises and sunsets ♪

49
00:04:17,620 --> 00:04:18,709
Yeah.

50
00:04:20,339 --> 00:04:24,190
♪ Have changed our original hearts ♪

51
00:04:24,620 --> 00:04:26,700
It's a pity there are no "ifs".

52
00:04:24,710 --> 00:04:27,810
♪ By not thinking about it or guessing ♪

53
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:31,100
♪ I thought I could break free ♪

54
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:37,590
♪ Time has shown
I'm not as carefree as I imagined ♪

55
00:04:39,850 --> 00:04:43,810
♪ I still can't forget the tenderness
you gave me that year ♪

56
00:04:43,870 --> 00:04:47,570
♪ Exhausting all my strength,
I still can't fool myself ♪

57
00:04:45,500 --> 00:04:46,620
Actually...

58
00:04:47,980 --> 00:04:51,070
♪ Your place is still here ♪

59
00:04:49,180 --> 00:04:51,380
I've been meaning to ask you

60
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:55,040
♪ No one else can take it ♪

61
00:04:51,380 --> 00:04:52,300
a question.

62
00:04:55,380 --> 00:04:56,940
After we split up,

63
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:59,390
♪ Let me treat it as just a heavy rain ♪

64
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:04,210
♪ Gradually, the memories we've built
become clear ♪

65
00:05:00,060 --> 00:05:01,380
how were you doing?

66
00:05:04,370 --> 00:05:08,730
♪ All composed into a song ♪

67
00:05:05,420 --> 00:05:06,330
Were you sad?

68
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:12,250
♪ Let me hide it in my heart ♪

69
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:15,400
♪ The one who was my only love ♪

70
00:05:14,740 --> 00:05:15,940
"Sad..."

71
00:05:15,530 --> 00:05:19,170
♪ Now becomes out of reach ♪

72
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:25,930
♪ Zooming out to find the trace ♪

73
00:05:21,900 --> 00:05:23,560
"Sad..."

74
00:05:26,270 --> 00:05:27,110
Yes, I was sad.

75
00:05:27,220 --> 00:05:31,120
♪ I still can't forget the tenderness
you gave me that year ♪\

76
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:34,830
♪ Exhausting all my strength,
I still can't fool myself ♪

77
00:05:34,909 --> 00:05:36,500
But I had to go on with my life, right?

78
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:38,300
♪ Your place is still here ♪

79
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:42,210
♪ No one else can take it ♪

80
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:46,659
♪ Let me treat it as just a heavy rain ♪

81
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:51,640
♪ Gradually, the memories we've built
become clear ♪

82
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:51,830
Do you remember

83
00:05:51,900 --> 00:05:56,260
♪ All composed into a song ♪

84
00:05:55,030 --> 00:05:57,450
a question that I once asked you?

85
00:05:56,470 --> 00:06:02,610
♪ Let me hide it in my heart ♪

86
00:05:59,030 --> 00:06:00,060
Tell me,

87
00:06:01,180 --> 00:06:02,790
what's the difference

88
00:06:03,620 --> 00:06:05,340
between friendship and love?

89
00:06:05,620 --> 00:06:07,180
Do you have an answer now?

90
00:06:24,270 --> 00:06:25,670
You can't give an answer,

91
00:06:26,710 --> 00:06:28,110
and I can't figure it out.

92
00:06:32,590 --> 00:06:33,980
Just as you said,

93
00:06:36,710 --> 00:06:38,770
people have to go on with their lives.

94
00:06:41,380 --> 00:06:42,590
You see,

95
00:06:43,350 --> 00:06:44,480
compared to misery,

96
00:06:46,790 --> 00:06:48,650
happiness matters more.

97
00:06:56,670 --> 00:06:57,470
At least...

98
00:07:02,710 --> 00:07:04,810
At least we are still friends now.

99
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:14,400
Right?

100
00:07:42,740 --> 00:07:44,340
The snow is getting heavier.

101
00:08:08,060 --> 00:08:08,830
This is it.

102
00:08:10,350 --> 00:08:10,980
Yeah.

103
00:08:12,470 --> 00:08:13,670
How about I pick you up

104
00:08:14,420 --> 00:08:15,820
for tomorrow's reunion?

105
00:08:16,590 --> 00:08:17,230
Okay.

106
00:08:17,980 --> 00:08:18,710
At what time?

107
00:08:20,630 --> 00:08:21,690
Ten in the morning.

108
00:08:22,150 --> 00:08:23,030
Don't be late.

109
00:08:29,980 --> 00:08:30,860
Well, then...

110
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:32,380
go to bed early.

111
00:08:33,549 --> 00:08:34,340
You too.

112
00:09:02,710 --> 00:09:03,500
Bye.

113
00:09:27,710 --> 00:09:28,240
Sister,

114
00:09:29,110 --> 00:09:31,510
were you kissing Xiaole just now?

115
00:09:36,020 --> 00:09:36,800
No.

116
00:09:37,230 --> 00:09:38,830
You must have been mistaken.

117
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:41,230
Don't spew nonsense.

118
00:09:43,380 --> 00:09:44,240
Go to sleep now!

119
00:09:48,260 --> 00:09:49,260
I was mistaken?

120
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:52,560
Then who was Xiaole kissing just now?

121
00:10:05,350 --> 00:10:06,580
You bought a car?

122
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:11,920
A second-hand one.

123
00:10:12,370 --> 00:10:13,500
It's not worth much.

124
00:10:21,780 --> 00:10:23,640
I can fasten the seatbelt myself.

125
00:10:27,020 --> 00:10:28,150
That's Xuan, right?

126
00:10:30,590 --> 00:10:32,520
What are you doing there, Brother?

127
00:10:34,470 --> 00:10:35,040
Sister.

128
00:10:36,020 --> 00:10:36,500
Sister,

129
00:10:36,580 --> 00:10:37,980
you look gorgeous today.

130
00:10:38,740 --> 00:10:39,830
Xiaole,

131
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:42,140
make sure you send my sister home safely.

132
00:10:42,140 --> 00:10:43,110
What else will I do?

133
00:10:43,110 --> 00:10:44,480
Kidnap her?

134
00:10:44,980 --> 00:10:45,620
Off you go.

135
00:10:48,390 --> 00:10:48,860
We're leaving.

136
00:10:48,860 --> 00:10:49,930
Uncle Dong, we're taking off!

137
00:10:49,930 --> 00:10:50,710
Go ahead!

138
00:10:58,380 --> 00:10:58,830
Dad,

139
00:11:00,230 --> 00:11:02,020
I think Xiaole is cheating.

140
00:11:02,020 --> 00:11:02,980
What's that gibberish now?

141
00:11:02,980 --> 00:11:04,620
Do you want me to hit you with this?

142
00:11:04,620 --> 00:11:05,260
Calm down.

143
00:11:05,290 --> 00:11:06,340
Tell me,

144
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:08,260
who taught you to badmouth others?

145
00:11:08,260 --> 00:11:10,060
Can't you learn something good?

146
00:11:10,860 --> 00:11:12,950
Dad, our neighbor Mr. Wang has already
gone for sword practice.

147
00:11:12,950 --> 00:11:14,110
You should catch up.

148
00:11:15,230 --> 00:11:16,420
Wang always

149
00:11:16,740 --> 00:11:18,200
tries to steal my thunder.

150
00:11:22,350 --> 00:11:23,950
Will you go first or should I?

151
00:11:24,020 --> 00:11:24,620
I'll go first.

152
00:11:24,620 --> 00:11:26,020
Okay. I'll beat you to it.

153
00:11:30,260 --> 00:11:31,830
W-What are you trying to do?

154
00:11:32,020 --> 00:11:32,480
That...

155
00:11:32,570 --> 00:11:33,450
was a sneak attack!

156
00:11:33,450 --> 00:11:34,390
A sneak attack!

157
00:11:38,390 --> 00:11:39,720
I've really got the hang

158
00:11:40,380 --> 00:11:42,470
of using this sword.

159
00:11:42,650 --> 00:11:43,870
It's a gift from Xiaole.

160
00:11:43,870 --> 00:11:45,400
He knows I enjoy playing it.

161
00:11:45,740 --> 00:11:46,470
Pfft.

162
00:11:47,620 --> 00:11:49,580
The sword my daughter bought me

163
00:11:49,660 --> 00:11:51,320
is the real deal.

164
00:11:51,500 --> 00:11:52,640
She's now...

165
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:53,830
working at a TV station.

166
00:11:53,830 --> 00:11:54,890
She's a pretty girl

167
00:11:54,900 --> 00:11:55,760
with a decent job.

168
00:11:55,760 --> 00:11:56,640
She's got

169
00:11:56,660 --> 00:11:57,940
loads of suitors,

170
00:11:57,970 --> 00:11:58,630
I'm telling you.

171
00:11:58,630 --> 00:11:59,990
Loads of suitors?

172
00:12:01,260 --> 00:12:02,250
Listen,

173
00:12:02,620 --> 00:12:03,650
Xiaole

174
00:12:03,740 --> 00:12:05,500
is a big-time photographer now.

175
00:12:05,500 --> 00:12:07,540
He has invited me to his next exhibition.

176
00:12:07,540 --> 00:12:08,540
Did you know that?

177
00:12:08,570 --> 00:12:09,350
You talk about...

178
00:12:09,350 --> 00:12:11,320
Xiaole all the time.

179
00:12:11,340 --> 00:12:13,540
Why do you never mention your daughter?

180
00:12:14,350 --> 00:12:17,640
My daughter is also very busy now.
You know?

181
00:12:17,860 --> 00:12:19,540
Xiaole and she will get

182
00:12:19,620 --> 00:12:20,730
engaged soon.

183
00:12:21,020 --> 00:12:21,550
Hey,

184
00:12:21,740 --> 00:12:22,990
don't jump to conclusions so soon.

185
00:12:22,990 --> 00:12:24,380
Nowadays, young people's relationships

186
00:12:24,380 --> 00:12:25,930
are never stable.

187
00:12:26,020 --> 00:12:29,020
They just keep breaking up
and getting back together.

188
00:12:29,140 --> 00:12:30,180
Don't you worry.

189
00:12:31,380 --> 00:12:32,360
Lan's relationship

190
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:33,500
with Xiaole is pretty solid.

191
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:34,740
To what extent, do you know?

192
00:12:34,740 --> 00:12:36,470
How do young people describe that now?

193
00:12:36,470 --> 00:12:36,950
They're

194
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:37,530
what is

195
00:12:37,660 --> 00:12:38,660
referred to as...

196
00:12:38,740 --> 00:12:39,720
"locked in"!

197
00:12:39,740 --> 00:12:40,300
You...

198
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:41,350
call that

199
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:42,290
"locked in"?

200
00:12:42,380 --> 00:12:44,440
They've been living apart for years.

201
00:12:44,780 --> 00:12:46,740
How can their relationship be stable?

202
00:12:46,740 --> 00:12:47,810
How?

203
00:12:48,900 --> 00:12:49,530
That's

204
00:12:49,550 --> 00:12:51,460
none of your concern!

205
00:12:51,740 --> 00:12:52,550
Right after

206
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:53,500
the next New Year,

207
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:54,440
they'll prepare

208
00:12:54,860 --> 00:12:55,860
to get engaged.

209
00:12:57,380 --> 00:12:58,550
Listen,

210
00:12:59,140 --> 00:13:00,320
don't be a petty man.

211
00:13:00,900 --> 00:13:03,260
You're welcome to their engagement party.

212
00:13:03,260 --> 00:13:04,720
I'm done playing with you.

213
00:13:05,230 --> 00:13:05,930
Wang,

214
00:13:06,580 --> 00:13:08,350
keep on with your sword practice.

215
00:13:08,350 --> 00:13:08,910
Bye!

216
00:13:17,110 --> 00:13:19,260
This is indeed a second-hand car.

217
00:13:22,470 --> 00:13:24,470
I'll get that fixed when I have time.

218
00:13:32,870 --> 00:13:34,720
J-J-Just leave it be for now.

219
00:13:38,350 --> 00:13:40,180
The window isn't broken, is it?

220
00:13:41,380 --> 00:13:42,110
No, it's not.

221
00:13:42,620 --> 00:13:43,350
It works.

222
00:13:47,020 --> 00:13:48,400
It's functioning now,

223
00:13:48,420 --> 00:13:51,350
but it won't be
if you keep fiddling with it like that.

224
00:14:00,190 --> 00:14:00,720
Yi Lan,

225
00:14:00,860 --> 00:14:01,860
I'm almost there.

226
00:14:03,140 --> 00:14:04,070
So am I.

227
00:14:06,380 --> 00:14:09,400
You seem quite close with Mark.

228
00:14:10,380 --> 00:14:11,620
He not only picked you up

229
00:14:11,620 --> 00:14:13,350
from the airport when you returned,

230
00:14:13,350 --> 00:14:14,850
and is now going out...

231
00:14:15,140 --> 00:14:15,940
with you. Huh?

232
00:14:16,010 --> 00:14:17,180
Are you jealous?

233
00:14:18,260 --> 00:14:19,790
Why would I be?

234
00:14:20,260 --> 00:14:23,120
As you said,
you've known each other for a long time.

235
00:14:23,350 --> 00:14:24,750
if you were into each other,

236
00:14:24,750 --> 00:14:26,620
you would've started dating already,
right?

237
00:14:26,620 --> 00:14:28,550
We didn't start dating
until we had been friends

238
00:14:28,550 --> 00:14:30,010
for over ten years, did we?

239
00:14:37,230 --> 00:14:38,140
Are you...

240
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,710
comparing me with him?

241
00:14:41,380 --> 00:14:42,580
Focus on the driving.

242
00:14:42,860 --> 00:14:44,520
He can't be compared with you.

243
00:14:54,140 --> 00:14:56,030
Lan!

244
00:14:56,140 --> 00:14:57,960
Long time no see!

245
00:14:58,470 --> 00:14:59,920
How come you've lost weight again?

246
00:14:59,920 --> 00:15:01,550
No way. I've gained weight lately.

247
00:15:01,550 --> 00:15:02,230
That's not true.

248
00:15:02,230 --> 00:15:04,160
What have you been up to these days?

249
00:15:04,970 --> 00:15:06,530
You're still into him?

250
00:15:06,620 --> 00:15:08,820
My idol's doing pretty well these days.

251
00:15:08,830 --> 00:15:10,270
I must learn from him

252
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:11,560
and focus on my career.

253
00:15:16,780 --> 00:15:18,100
Tong Xiaole!

254
00:15:18,470 --> 00:15:19,510
So you can see me.

255
00:15:19,540 --> 00:15:21,000
I thought I was invisible.

256
00:15:21,740 --> 00:15:23,090
The two of you...

257
00:15:23,110 --> 00:15:24,240
We're good friends.

258
00:15:27,020 --> 00:15:28,170
"Good friends..."

259
00:15:28,660 --> 00:15:31,590
It's that "childhood friends" story
all over again.

260
00:15:31,900 --> 00:15:35,160
Let me take a look
at this little musical instrument store.

261
00:15:35,900 --> 00:15:37,410
It hasn't changed much.

262
00:15:37,550 --> 00:15:38,960
Well managed, I'd say.

263
00:15:39,950 --> 00:15:40,600
Mengmeng.

264
00:15:40,620 --> 00:15:41,050
Yes?

265
00:15:41,070 --> 00:15:43,280
Is Shan coming back?

266
00:15:43,910 --> 00:15:46,290
Shan and Professor Ye are legally
registered husband and wife now.

267
00:15:46,290 --> 00:15:46,620
Yeah.

268
00:15:46,630 --> 00:15:47,960
It's news to you, right?

269
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:49,070
They're married?

270
00:15:49,070 --> 00:15:50,700
No wonder they're selling this store.

271
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:52,180
Will they settle abroad?

272
00:15:53,180 --> 00:15:55,230
Where did you pop up from, Zhao Zhenghao?

273
00:15:55,230 --> 00:15:57,180
H-Haven't the two of you broken up?

274
00:15:57,260 --> 00:15:58,140
Yeah,

275
00:15:58,140 --> 00:15:59,230
we have.

276
00:15:59,470 --> 00:16:00,190
Mengmeng,

277
00:16:00,470 --> 00:16:01,600
haven't you told Lan

278
00:16:01,620 --> 00:16:03,260
the truth over all these years?

279
00:16:03,260 --> 00:16:05,330
Told me what?
Did you get back with Zhao Zhenghao?

280
00:16:05,330 --> 00:16:06,930
No, I didn't.

281
00:16:06,960 --> 00:16:08,270
We're not kids anymore.

282
00:16:08,270 --> 00:16:10,070
My priority now is to make money.

283
00:16:10,110 --> 00:16:12,290
Zhao Zhenghao and I
are just business partners.

284
00:16:12,290 --> 00:16:12,860
Yes!

285
00:16:13,190 --> 00:16:15,070
Mengmeng provides ideas,
while I do the work.

286
00:16:15,070 --> 00:16:17,070
With her creativity and my execution,

287
00:16:17,070 --> 00:16:20,030
our business will be booming and thriving.

288
00:16:20,230 --> 00:16:22,220
We're planning to start a small business
together.

289
00:16:22,220 --> 00:16:24,080
What do you think? Care to join us?

290
00:16:25,050 --> 00:16:26,600
Do you two need an investor?

291
00:16:26,620 --> 00:16:27,490
That guy's rich.

292
00:16:27,490 --> 00:16:28,150
Turn to him.

293
00:16:30,860 --> 00:16:31,950
It's about time.

294
00:16:31,980 --> 00:16:33,380
We should go to the restaurant now.

295
00:16:33,380 --> 00:16:34,310
No, not now.

296
00:16:34,340 --> 00:16:36,020
My friend's coming over for a visit.

297
00:16:36,020 --> 00:16:36,530
Lan.

298
00:16:37,380 --> 00:16:38,060
Mark!

299
00:16:38,900 --> 00:16:39,830
This is the place.

300
00:16:39,830 --> 00:16:41,560
Let me introduce you to each other.

301
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:42,550
This is Mark.

302
00:16:42,550 --> 00:16:43,870
This is my best friend, Mengmeng.

303
00:16:43,870 --> 00:16:44,290
Hello.

304
00:16:44,310 --> 00:16:46,730
Zhenghao here went to high school with us.

305
00:16:46,780 --> 00:16:47,710
Hello, Mr. Mark.

306
00:16:47,860 --> 00:16:48,900
And this

307
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:49,850
is...

308
00:16:49,900 --> 00:16:51,260
I've met him. He's no stranger to me.

309
00:16:51,260 --> 00:16:51,870
Yes.

310
00:16:52,560 --> 00:16:53,980
How about a tour?

311
00:16:54,390 --> 00:16:55,440
This musical instrument store

312
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:57,240
used to be owned by a luthier.

313
00:16:57,260 --> 00:17:00,140
That's why there are luthier tools around.

314
00:17:00,260 --> 00:17:03,230
Over here is some equipment,

315
00:17:03,260 --> 00:17:04,220
and new devices.

316
00:17:04,380 --> 00:17:07,400
These are guitars and vinyls.

317
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:08,470
There's a room here.

318
00:17:08,470 --> 00:17:09,520
Come in for a visit.

319
00:17:09,520 --> 00:17:09,990
Sure.

320
00:17:10,460 --> 00:17:12,260
The soundproofing is very good.

321
00:17:12,310 --> 00:17:14,440
One can practice instruments in here.

322
00:17:14,829 --> 00:17:16,440
All the equipment is new.

323
00:17:19,790 --> 00:17:22,109
When Lan was abroad, that foreigner tried

324
00:17:22,109 --> 00:17:23,910
to make all sorts of moves on her.

325
00:17:24,109 --> 00:17:26,220
He'll probably target Mengmeng later...

326
00:17:26,220 --> 00:17:27,109
Just you watch.

327
00:17:28,380 --> 00:17:29,520
What do you think?

328
00:17:38,990 --> 00:17:41,430
Will all the instruments and vinyls stay?

329
00:17:42,510 --> 00:17:43,210
Yes,

330
00:17:43,270 --> 00:17:44,860
they all come with the store.

331
00:17:44,860 --> 00:17:45,600
To be honest,

332
00:17:45,940 --> 00:17:49,140
I'm very satisfied with
the location and the furnishing.

333
00:17:49,550 --> 00:17:52,110
Let's go over the contract details
when available.

334
00:17:52,110 --> 00:17:52,940
Sure.

335
00:17:53,110 --> 00:17:55,080
Let's meet up in private sometime.

336
00:17:59,550 --> 00:18:01,010
I'm her business partner.

337
00:18:01,860 --> 00:18:02,720
See you around.

338
00:18:04,420 --> 00:18:05,030
Okay.

339
00:18:09,030 --> 00:18:09,640
Lan,

340
00:18:09,990 --> 00:18:11,340
I'll surely pay you

341
00:18:11,360 --> 00:18:12,350
a referral fee.

342
00:18:12,460 --> 00:18:14,320
We're friends. Don't mention it.

343
00:18:14,350 --> 00:18:16,980
Does it mean you'll settle in the country?

344
00:18:17,070 --> 00:18:17,810
Yes.

345
00:18:18,110 --> 00:18:19,420
After living abroad for so long,

346
00:18:19,420 --> 00:18:20,810
I truly miss home.

347
00:18:21,510 --> 00:18:23,070
Shall we have dinner tonight?

348
00:18:23,070 --> 00:18:23,870
Sorry,

349
00:18:23,940 --> 00:18:25,870
we already have plans for tonight.

350
00:18:26,350 --> 00:18:27,030
Oh.

351
00:18:27,750 --> 00:18:29,950
You guys are having a gathering, right?

352
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:32,590
Alright, everyone.

353
00:18:32,590 --> 00:18:35,390
I need to go for
an important business meeting now.

354
00:18:35,420 --> 00:18:36,030
Let's hang out sometime.

355
00:18:36,030 --> 00:18:36,980
Take care.

356
00:18:37,270 --> 00:18:38,800
The elevator is over there.

357
00:18:39,140 --> 00:18:40,270
I'll stop here then.

358
00:18:42,840 --> 00:18:45,330
That Mark guy...

359
00:18:45,510 --> 00:18:46,810
he has a fiancée.

360
00:18:47,550 --> 00:18:49,180
Don't be fooled by the way he behaves.

361
00:18:49,180 --> 00:18:50,620
He's actually quite nice.

362
00:18:50,620 --> 00:18:51,620
He's a good guy.

363
00:18:51,990 --> 00:18:54,780
Good guys are usually taken, aren't they?

364
00:18:54,860 --> 00:18:55,960
How's he a good guy?

365
00:18:56,140 --> 00:18:56,920
Yeah.

366
00:18:57,170 --> 00:18:58,410
This so called good guy

367
00:18:58,410 --> 00:18:59,810
once pursued Yi Lan.

368
00:18:59,880 --> 00:19:01,690
Hard to believe he already got a fiancée
within the short time

369
00:19:01,690 --> 00:19:02,620
he's been back to the country.

370
00:19:02,620 --> 00:19:03,280
Right, Lan?

371
00:19:03,830 --> 00:19:05,300
Alright. Let's go for dinner.

372
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:06,830
Ningning is waiting for us.

373
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:11,390
Hey, Tong.

374
00:19:11,410 --> 00:19:11,790
Yes?

375
00:19:12,110 --> 00:19:14,040
Why not try to win Lan back?

376
00:19:14,590 --> 00:19:17,140
Stop keeping each other
from dating new people.

377
00:19:17,140 --> 00:19:18,870
It's going to be torture again.

378
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:20,430
I'm tired of watching this.

379
00:19:22,750 --> 00:19:24,350
You'll have to watch anyway.

380
00:19:30,490 --> 00:19:31,100
Xiaole.

381
00:19:33,460 --> 00:19:34,590
This car of yours...

382
00:19:36,270 --> 00:19:37,200
is a bit cramped.

383
00:19:39,510 --> 00:19:41,590
You guys have never been in a sports car,
have you?

384
00:19:41,590 --> 00:19:43,350
This is what the layout is usually like.

385
00:19:43,350 --> 00:19:44,970
You call this a sports car?

386
00:19:44,990 --> 00:19:47,280
I was in Chen Fan's sports car once
back in high school.

387
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:48,210
Qiao Mengmeng,

388
00:19:48,260 --> 00:19:49,760
if you're willing to stay,

389
00:19:49,790 --> 00:19:51,160
sit there at ease.

390
00:19:51,270 --> 00:19:52,750
If not,

391
00:19:52,770 --> 00:19:55,030
you're welcome to get out and take a taxi.

392
00:19:55,510 --> 00:19:56,510
Let's get out of this car.

393
00:19:56,510 --> 00:19:57,840
Fine, let's hail a taxi.

394
00:20:01,580 --> 00:20:03,110
Why are you still in the car?

395
00:20:05,990 --> 00:20:07,190
We're make do with it.

396
00:20:07,270 --> 00:20:08,730
I don't want to get out now.

397
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:12,400
See?

398
00:20:12,420 --> 00:20:14,380
I told you not to take this road.

399
00:20:14,550 --> 00:20:15,960
Look how jammed it is now.

400
00:20:16,030 --> 00:20:17,200
You're not the one driving.

401
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:18,530
Why boss Xiaole around?

402
00:20:18,950 --> 00:20:20,730
Let him keep his dignity.

403
00:20:20,790 --> 00:20:23,170
What does his dignity have to do with you?

404
00:20:23,220 --> 00:20:24,070
Do you have to butt in?

405
00:20:24,070 --> 00:20:25,670
Are you asking for a beating?

406
00:20:25,750 --> 00:20:27,510
I'm your one and only business partner.

407
00:20:27,510 --> 00:20:29,220
Where will you find a fool to work with
if you beat me away?

408
00:20:29,220 --> 00:20:31,160
-I'll never work with a fool.
-This is enough.

409
00:20:31,160 --> 00:20:32,240
Stop quarreling.

410
00:20:32,510 --> 00:20:34,110
Thank God you two don't own a car.

411
00:20:34,110 --> 00:20:35,790
This is actually them on a good day.

412
00:20:35,790 --> 00:20:37,310
You haven't seen them...

413
00:20:37,860 --> 00:20:38,990
get in a real fight.

414
00:20:39,620 --> 00:20:41,130
You hit Mengmeng?

415
00:20:41,820 --> 00:20:43,220
I was the one being hit.

416
00:20:43,700 --> 00:20:46,500
Stop spreading rumors,
or I'll rip your mouth off.

417
00:20:55,070 --> 00:20:56,280
Chen Fan, what's up?

418
00:20:56,830 --> 00:20:58,050
We're stuck in traffic.

419
00:20:58,050 --> 00:20:59,110
Where are you guys?

420
00:20:59,220 --> 00:21:00,500
We're also stuck.

421
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:01,490
Where are you?

422
00:21:02,220 --> 00:21:03,670
Oh, we're on Xinyun Road.

423
00:21:04,550 --> 00:21:06,660
We're near our high school now, aren't we?

424
00:21:06,660 --> 00:21:07,400
Shall we...

425
00:21:07,420 --> 00:21:08,650
go there for a visit?

426
00:21:08,790 --> 00:21:09,760
-Okay.
-Okay.

427
00:21:09,900 --> 00:21:11,430
You heard that, didn't you?

428
00:21:11,510 --> 00:21:12,140
Alright.

429
00:21:12,350 --> 00:21:13,640
It's settled then.

430
00:21:14,290 --> 00:21:14,860
Okay.

431
00:21:29,220 --> 00:21:30,990
Look at this cute couple!

432
00:21:30,990 --> 00:21:32,250
-How sweet.
-Ning!

433
00:21:33,830 --> 00:21:34,700
Lan.

434
00:21:35,660 --> 00:21:36,460
Mengmeng.

435
00:21:36,460 --> 00:21:38,460
-Long time no see.
-It really has been long.

436
00:21:38,460 --> 00:21:40,090
Good to see you again.

437
00:21:41,420 --> 00:21:42,270
Mr. Chen!

438
00:21:42,590 --> 00:21:44,560
Where are you making your millions now?

439
00:21:44,560 --> 00:21:46,550
What a tacky greeting.

440
00:21:46,750 --> 00:21:47,970
When did you come back?

441
00:21:47,970 --> 00:21:48,800
You didn't even tell me.

442
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:50,350
Haven't you been busy rehearsing?

443
00:21:50,350 --> 00:21:51,830
You've become prettier again!

444
00:21:51,830 --> 00:21:54,260
-So have you.
-You too.

445
00:21:54,590 --> 00:21:55,540
Concertmaster Luo,

446
00:21:55,540 --> 00:21:56,630
long time no see.

447
00:21:56,900 --> 00:21:57,640
Chen Fan!

448
00:21:58,550 --> 00:22:01,590
You two are still inseparable
even though you've broken up.

449
00:22:01,590 --> 00:22:03,190
Why not just get married?

450
00:22:05,060 --> 00:22:06,640
He's my chauffeur today.

451
00:22:07,500 --> 00:22:08,160
Ignore him.

452
00:22:08,180 --> 00:22:08,710
Let's go.

453
00:22:11,050 --> 00:22:13,330
Luo Ningzi is doing really well lately.

454
00:22:13,350 --> 00:22:15,010
She's completely sober now.

455
00:22:15,030 --> 00:22:17,070
Of course she's getting better and better.

456
00:22:17,070 --> 00:22:17,880
Really?

457
00:22:19,030 --> 00:22:21,030
Maybe it's time I quit drinking too.

458
00:22:25,540 --> 00:22:27,850
The school looks just the same as before.

459
00:22:30,620 --> 00:22:32,360
Thank God we chose to come at this time.

460
00:22:32,360 --> 00:22:33,280
It's warmer than other times.

461
00:22:33,280 --> 00:22:35,410
The wind was biting cold this morning.

462
00:22:35,700 --> 00:22:37,300
-Such broad daylight.
-It's also cold now.

463
00:22:37,300 --> 00:22:38,500
There's no vibe here.

464
00:22:38,510 --> 00:22:41,510
The romance only kicks in
when we watch stars at night.

465
00:22:41,590 --> 00:22:42,320
Put these on.

466
00:22:42,700 --> 00:22:43,470
It's windy.

467
00:22:44,460 --> 00:22:45,240
Thanks.

468
00:22:46,180 --> 00:22:47,790
You're still treating your ex-girlfriend
so well.

469
00:22:47,790 --> 00:22:48,950
Are you still hung up on her?

470
00:22:48,950 --> 00:22:50,280
Stop talking nonsense.

471
00:22:50,750 --> 00:22:53,010
They are neighbors who grew up together.

472
00:22:53,070 --> 00:22:54,790
What's wrong with showing care
to each other?

473
00:22:54,790 --> 00:22:57,100
Look how considerate Xiaole is.

474
00:22:57,900 --> 00:22:59,420
I don't have any gloves on.

475
00:22:59,460 --> 00:23:01,860
How is it my fault
that you didn't bring any?

476
00:23:05,110 --> 00:23:06,420
They're acting up again.

477
00:23:06,420 --> 00:23:08,410
I must make lots and lots of money
this year!

478
00:23:08,410 --> 00:23:10,490
I want tons of money!

479
00:23:12,460 --> 00:23:14,030
Are they on it again?

480
00:23:14,090 --> 00:23:15,300
God, let me make a fortune,

481
00:23:15,300 --> 00:23:17,560
without paying heavy costs!

482
00:23:18,300 --> 00:23:20,230
That's why they were once a couple.

483
00:23:23,030 --> 00:23:24,510
Why that laugh?
Aren't you going to make a wish?

484
00:23:24,510 --> 00:23:25,170
Yes, I am.

485
00:23:25,790 --> 00:23:29,590
I hope my friends and family will all stay
happy and healthy forever!

486
00:23:30,460 --> 00:23:31,320
As for me...

487
00:23:31,460 --> 00:23:34,540
I hope my orchestra can shine bright
on the stage

488
00:23:34,560 --> 00:23:35,570
and receive more applause.

489
00:23:35,570 --> 00:23:37,420
And I wish for everything my fiancée said
to come true!

490
00:23:37,420 --> 00:23:38,260
"Fiancée"?

491
00:23:38,350 --> 00:23:39,590
"Fiancée"?

492
00:23:41,970 --> 00:23:43,300
We're getting married.

493
00:23:44,350 --> 00:23:45,900
I'll be your future children's godmother.

494
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:47,500
I'll be their godmother too.

495
00:23:47,510 --> 00:23:48,640
Then I'll be...

496
00:23:48,660 --> 00:23:49,870
their godfather.

497
00:23:51,990 --> 00:23:54,070
She decides when we will have children.

498
00:23:54,070 --> 00:23:56,320
You're pretty enlightened now.

499
00:23:56,750 --> 00:23:57,480
Well then...

500
00:23:58,170 --> 00:23:59,490
My fiancé is right.

501
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:01,710
Come on, while we're here,

502
00:24:01,710 --> 00:24:04,040
let me take a photo
of you two loving birds.

503
00:24:06,380 --> 00:24:07,230
Cheese.

504
00:24:07,260 --> 00:24:07,940
Count me in!

505
00:24:08,270 --> 00:24:08,990
Me too!

506
00:24:11,250 --> 00:24:11,810
Three.

507
00:24:11,950 --> 00:24:12,630
Two.

508
00:24:12,650 --> 00:24:13,280
One.

509
00:24:21,510 --> 00:24:22,880
What are they doing?

510
00:24:28,990 --> 00:24:30,940
Haven't you met anyone new?

511
00:24:31,550 --> 00:24:33,100
My love life...

512
00:24:33,700 --> 00:24:35,100
is basically dead.

513
00:24:38,110 --> 00:24:38,970
What about you?

514
00:24:39,160 --> 00:24:40,470
Haven't you met anyone new?

515
00:24:40,470 --> 00:24:41,320
Me?

516
00:24:44,350 --> 00:24:45,280
Venture a guess.

517
00:24:48,270 --> 00:24:49,400
Of course I haven't.

518
00:24:50,030 --> 00:24:51,270
But you and Xiaole...

519
00:24:51,570 --> 00:24:54,310
are having this push-and-pull thing
going on.

520
00:24:54,580 --> 00:24:55,390
What is it for?

521
00:24:55,660 --> 00:24:57,690
What "push-and-pull thing"?

522
00:24:57,720 --> 00:24:58,350
Mengmeng,

523
00:24:58,620 --> 00:24:59,770
you don't get it.

524
00:24:59,790 --> 00:25:02,460
This is what couples do.
They just push and pull.

525
00:25:02,660 --> 00:25:03,660
Look at me and Chen Fan.

526
00:25:03,660 --> 00:25:05,660
I want to cancel the engagement now.

527
00:25:14,110 --> 00:25:14,800
Lan.

528
00:25:15,790 --> 00:25:17,330
Do you think

529
00:25:18,270 --> 00:25:20,050
you will ever meet someone

530
00:25:21,220 --> 00:25:22,490
more suited for you

531
00:25:23,290 --> 00:25:24,700
than Xiaole?

532
00:25:33,670 --> 00:25:34,350
This is it.

533
00:25:35,120 --> 00:25:35,920
Goodbye then.

534
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:37,440
I should go too.

535
00:25:40,870 --> 00:25:41,440
Yi Lan!

536
00:25:41,470 --> 00:25:42,040
Yes?

537
00:25:44,750 --> 00:25:45,770
During your stay,

538
00:25:45,990 --> 00:25:47,990
let me know if there's any place

539
00:25:48,010 --> 00:25:48,940
you'd like to go.

540
00:25:49,070 --> 00:25:49,850
I can

541
00:25:49,940 --> 00:25:50,950
go with you.

542
00:25:53,180 --> 00:25:55,410
I'll tell you when I come up with an idea.

543
00:25:55,590 --> 00:25:56,020
Okay.

544
00:26:01,140 --> 00:26:02,010
Have you not

545
00:26:02,030 --> 00:26:04,370
visited my family since you came back?

546
00:26:05,750 --> 00:26:06,380
Right.

547
00:26:06,810 --> 00:26:09,010
-What about...
-What about a visit now?

548
00:26:11,700 --> 00:26:12,580
Sure.

549
00:26:12,700 --> 00:26:14,340
I'll set off to your place

550
00:26:14,420 --> 00:26:15,520
after getting

551
00:26:16,140 --> 00:26:16,670
changed.

552
00:26:17,590 --> 00:26:18,720
I-I'll wait for you.

553
00:26:29,550 --> 00:26:31,210
I'm good. You keep going.

554
00:26:31,510 --> 00:26:32,020
Dad.

555
00:26:32,420 --> 00:26:32,950
Mom.

556
00:26:36,180 --> 00:26:37,180
Careful. Slowly.

557
00:26:37,220 --> 00:26:37,650
Where

558
00:26:37,680 --> 00:26:38,770
are you going?

559
00:26:39,750 --> 00:26:41,220
I'm taking your dad out for a stroll.

560
00:26:41,220 --> 00:26:42,450
Since you're here,

561
00:26:42,480 --> 00:26:43,500
why don't you take him out instead?

562
00:26:43,500 --> 00:26:44,460
I'll tidy up our home.

563
00:26:44,460 --> 00:26:46,720
Mom, Lan is coming over later.

564
00:26:46,830 --> 00:26:49,090
What are you afraid of with me being home?

565
00:26:49,270 --> 00:26:50,200
Go out for a walk.

566
00:26:50,220 --> 00:26:51,750
Come on. Take a walk with me.

567
00:26:52,070 --> 00:26:52,620
Okay.

568
00:26:52,830 --> 00:26:53,780
Careful.

569
00:26:54,270 --> 00:26:55,750
Mom, wait at home.

570
00:26:55,790 --> 00:26:57,160
Got it. Don't worry.
